cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with image classification and uses convolutional layers to extract visual features. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a novel deep learning architecture to classify structured objects and jointly learns parameters from both local-visual features and neighboring classes. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new approach to overcome the difficulties of existing CRF methods to learn contextual relationships thoroughly when there is a large number of classes and the data is sparse. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with structured objects and uses a linear-chain CRF to model sequences of images. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image datasets and proposes a new deep learning architecture for image classification.
